    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2012-02-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2012-05-25T19:34:32Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Prompt Notification of Short Sales Act - Requires each servicer of a home mortgage to respond in writing within 75 days to a mortgagor of a residential mortgage loan who has requested in writing a short sale of the dwelling or residential real property that is subject to the mortgage, deed of trust, or other security interest securing the mortgage loan.</p> <p>Authorizes an aggrieved individual to bring a civil action for damages and equitable relief for any violation of this Act.</p> <p>Declares this Act inapplicable to certain residential mortgages entered into before its enactment whose mortgage agreements explicitly provide a procedure or terms for a short sale approval.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Prompt Notification of Short Sales Act</title>
